name: Iris-dataset-predict-the-optimum-number-of-clusters-and-represent
description: To predict the optimum number of clusters for the Iris dataset and visualize it, we use the K-means clustering algorithm. The steps involve loading and preprocessing the data, determining the best 'k' using methods like the Elbow Method or Silhouette Score, applying K-means clustering, and finally, visualizing the clusters with different colors .

name: Gaussian-Mixture-Model
description: we use Gaussian Mixture Model (GMM) as a clustering algorithm to segmentate the pixels of a picture, and also we replace value of points of each segment with value of corresponded centroid.

name: COVID-19-Time-Series-Clustering-and-Analysis
description: Focuses on Wisconsin and California to gain insights into the COVID-19 death patterns in these states. Performs hierarchical clustering using both single linkage and complete linkage, along with K-means clustering to group states based on parameter estimates

name: K-means-for-Rugby-Social-Team-Making-
description: NLP & K-means for making teams and friends at a Rugby Social

name: Anomaly-Detection-in-Transactions-and-Netflow-logs
description: In this project, Cloud Dataflow streaming pipelines leverage BigQuery ML and Cloud AI Platform to detect anomalies in real-time netflow logs for Telco cybersecurity and identify fraudulent transactions in Financial Services. The system empowers timely responses to potential threats and enhances data-driven decision-making for both industries.
